column10: I don’t know how she didn’t hit me. Her light was red and she rolled through the crosswalk. She apologized.
This being the entrance/exit  to Old town, it is a very stretgic location to advise drivers they are entering a pedestrian priority zone!!

Appx 2:45 EDT 7/5/21 Amazon driver of white Ford Transit departed condo park if lot, failed to stop at the stop sign & yield to the pedestrian entering the crosswalk (me). Driver proceeded to accelerate westbound Slaters LN.

Motorist northbound, left lane, on N Washington St sped through red light after pedestrians (myself and another) entered crosswalk. The walk signal was on and right lane traffic stopped. Not the first time I have witnessed this action at this location.

I was nearly hit while in the crosswalk by a van traveling at well over 50mph and running the red-light. The light had been red long enough for me to check for approaching cars to stop. The van was going so fast that I didn't even see it until too late; Running

Car traveling south on N Washington Street ran the red light as I waited to cross at Slaters Lane. Two other pedestrians were waiting to cross on the opposite side closest to  southbound traffic. The vehicle passed us after the walk signal indicated that it was safe for us to enter the crosswalk. This occurs regularly at this intersection.
